reviewText: Pretty. Thin. Maintain a nice luster. Very light in weight. Received as expected. The size is adequate. Blah, blah, blah.

I'm a typical guy that is basically clueless about jewelry, but I can certainly appreciate the ease of buying something on Amazon as opposed to going to a jewelry store and dealing with salespeople trying to push expensive products. My favorite move is when they take out their calculator and magically apply some unknown discount to what may or may not be a sticker price. My wife absolutely loved these earings - I don't know exactly why - but if your loved one is asking for gold hoop earrings these are the real deal.

Like others, I felt the clasp was too fragile. Also, I'm short and found them to be too large for me. They are very pretty. And, for the price, if they hadn't been to large for my body, I would have kept them.
These earrings I had to send back because they weren't that big like I wanted them to be and they were flimsy and for the price I expected to be a bolder look, and a heavier weight.
These are shiny and made very well.Very haute couture and more soif you wear them in graduated sizes, at thesame time.
summary: BUY THESE U WILL HAVE NO REGRETS !

reviewText: At least for me, these are the perfect size. The color is great. They're just as pictured. Light and comfortable to wear, you can see them well and they have enuogh size to have some style, but still not oversized.
They're good, very simple,good quality, they were a gift and she seemed very pleased with the earrings. I don't know what else to say.

reviewerName: Michelle L. Beck Always the Devourer of Good...
reviewText: My husband purchased these for my birthday in December, and I really love them. They are light weight, thin,they stay closed and they are not too big. If you are in the market for a lovely pair of hoop earrings. These are absolutely perfect.

The reviews on these earrings were so mixed that I wasn't sure I was going to be happy when I received them. I'm pleased to say I was not unpleasantly surprised.They are flimsy, they're very light, they don't seem overly trustworthy, but they're very pretty AND under $150. If you're looking for solid heavy gold hoops that will last a lifetime, you need to visit your jeweler and be prepared to invest. If you want a delicate pair of chic hoops that will fill a hole in your jewelry box for less than the cost of a nice dinner out, these are for you.

I've went through several gold hoops before settling on these. They're the perfect size - not too big, not too small. My only complaint is that the closure bends very easily. I feel like I'm going to brake them every time I take them off.
